"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-09-paris-2024-officials-issue-response-second-olympian-criticises-tarnished-medals-21397358\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris2024 officials have issued a response after a secondOlympicathlete raised concerns over the deterioration of their bronze medal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paris2024 officials\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 19}, {\"ngram\": \"a response\", \"from\": 32, \"to\": 42}, {\"ngram\": \"secondOlympicathlete\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 71}, {\"ngram\": \"the deterioration\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 110}, {\"ngram\": \"their bronze medal\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals at the Paris Games, which eachcontain scrap metal taken from the Eiffel Tower, first came under fire after a video posted by American athlete Nyjah Huston on Thursday.\", \"from\": 135, \"to\": 313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999367592154, \"rank\": 3.100160705881325e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nyjah Huston\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medals\", \"from\": 135, \"to\": 145}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"scrap metal\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 195}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 242, \"to\": 246}, {\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The skateboardershowed the visible change in the colour of his medal,which had also begun to chip, and suggested they were 'not as high quality as you would think'.\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 479, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the visible change\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 356}, {\"ngram\": \"the colour\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"his medal\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 383}, {\"ngram\": \"as high quality\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's looking rough,' he added.\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 512, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Even the front is starting to chip off a little.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even the front\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I do not know, Olympic medals, we gotta step up the quality a little bit.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medal [is] looking like it went to war and back.'\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medal\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, Team GB diver Yasmin Harper has claimed her bronze medal,won alongside Scarlett Mew Jensen in the women's 3m synchronised diving contest, is also showing signs of deterioration.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9991204344259818, \"rank\": 0.00044814393959111777, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her bronze medal\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"signs\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 858}, {\"ngram\": \"deterioration\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'There has been some small bits of tarnishing, I will admit,' the Brit said after finishing fifth in the 3m springboard final on Friday.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 1014, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some small bits\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"tarnishing\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 923}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brit\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the 3m\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's going a little bit.\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it's if water or anything gets under it, it makes it go a little bit discoloured, but I am not sure.'\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1075}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the claims, Paris officials have put out a statement saying that they will work with affected athletes to ensure a swift replacement medal is given out.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999968624707, \"rank\": 3.1376064943625917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"the claims\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1220}, {\"ngram\": \"affected athletes\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"a swift replacement medal\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Paris 2024 is working closely with the Monnaie de Paris, the institution tasked with the production and quality control of the medals, and together with the national Olympic committee of the athlete concerned, in order to appraise the medal to understand the circumstances and cause of the damage,' the statement read.\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 4.953476439102141e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1362, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monnaie de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the institution\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"the production and quality control\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"the national Olympic committee\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"the athlete\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"the circumstances\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"cause\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"the damage\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"the statement\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The medals are the most coveted objects of the Games and the most precious for the athletes.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medals\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"the most coveted objects\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Damaged medals will be systematically replaced by the Monnaie de Paris and engraved in an identical way to the originals.'\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1793, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monnaie de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Damaged medals\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1753}, {\"ngram\": \"an identical way\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"the originals\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medals, which appear to be the only ones affected thus far, contain copper, zinc, tin, and traces of silver.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bronze medals\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1880}, {\"ngram\": \"the only ones\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1914}, {\"ngram\": \"copper\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1948}, {\"ngram\": \"zinc\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1954}, {\"ngram\": \"tin\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"traces\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more stories\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"our sport page\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2031}]}, {\"sentence